WHAT IS PUIC?
  Puic is a USB image creator for Pardus 2008 or later. You can write
  image to USB disk from any Pardus 2008 or later ISO image.

REQUIREMENTS
  python >= 2.5
  syslinux > 3.82.1
  mtools

INSTALLATION
  Now, puic is not stable and still it has not any graphical
  interface. So it is not at Pardus repositories, now. But you can
  package it your Pardus and install this package for using puic.
  Therefore:

  # pisi bi http://svn.pardus.org.tr/pardus/playground/ggorgen/puic/pspec.xml
  # pisi it puic*.pisi

TRANSLATION
  For translators:
      $ cd $(PUIC)/po
      $ msginit -l $(LANG)

  For developers:
      $ cd $(PUIC)/po
      $ xgettext -f POTFILES.in ../puic.py -L Python --output=puic.pot